 eye along the spring that cascades into a frosty stream. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Evening stroll near the spring Picnic with family and friends Loosen up in its calm environment 2. Garam Sadak It is a route in the Dalhousie that link Gandhi Chowk with Subhash Chowk and is amongst the undiscovered locations to explore in the small town. Visitors can enjoy the valley's picturesque view from the Thai road fringed with tall trees and luxurious greenery. Wandering around in this place is considered the most touristy thing to do in the town. In addition, visitors will be able to see extraordinary Tibetan Rock Paintings sculpted on the walls on the wayside. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Witness incredible scenes of the valley A leisurely stroll Watch beautiful Tibetan Rock Paintings carved on the roadside 3. Panchpula Panchpula is a preferred picnic area in the town, placed 3.5 KM far away from the shopping market, Gandhi Chowk. Surrounded by a blanket of pine and deodar trees, it is famous for the Saptdhara waterfalls, which is the Ganji Pahari trek's starting point. A Samadhi or monument is also erected nearby this place to memorialize Sardar Ajit Singh (martyr Bhagat Singh's uncle), a rebellious and revolutionary. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry fee - No entry fee Activities to enjoy at the place: Ziplining Trekking Burma Bridge Taste local snacks and tea 4. John's Church St. John's Church was built back in 1863 and is the oldest church in the town. This church is a perfect mix of history and beauty and is considered one of the best attractions to explore in Dalhousie. It is quite popular amongst photographers due to its beautiful construction. On Sunday, various locals and visitors assemble at this church to witness the performance of the Sunday Service. As this place is also a reminder of the British rule in the region, it is admired by history lovers. In addition, the church showcases architecture embellished with glass paintings of St John the Baptist together with St Peter. Opening hours - 7:00 am to 7:00 pm Entry fee - No entry fee Activities to enjoy at the place: Photography Acquire knowledge about historical events Be present at Sunday Service See the beautiful glass paintings and impressive architectonics 5. Gandhi Chowk (Mall Road) GPO or Gandhi Chowk is a place in Dalhousie to enjoy a shopping tour and is a mall road in this small town. Visitors can buy traditional handicrafts from local markets and take gifts for themselves and their loved ones. The Himachal Handloom Industry Emporium and the Tibetan Market are among some of the famous shops at Gandhi Chowk from where one can buy memento, woolen clothes and much more. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Explore the Emporium on Thandi Sarak Buy traditional handiwork and keepsakes Pay a visit to Bhittico to get Kullu shawls, pashmina and angora 6. Ganji Pahari Ganji Pahari in Dalhousie offers its visitors an astounding view of snow-topped peaks. One has to trek to reach the peak that begins from Panchpula, and as this trek is easy to moderate, anyone can do it. Also named Bald Hill, Ganji Pahari is popular for its complete absence of vegetation on the hillock. Tourists can plan their winter trip to see a thick blanket of snow covering this hillock. Explore Ganji Pahari during dawn or sundown for the best experience. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Trekking Camping (advance booking is required) Watch eye-catching views of mountains 7. Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary has a wide range of luxurious meadows, thick deodar foliage, freshwater streams and more, making it a must-visit tourist attraction in the town for wildlife admirers. Kalatop means "black cap", which refers to the black 