t Peter. Opening hours - 7:00 am to 7:00 pm Entry fee - No entry fee Activities to enjoy at the place: Photography Acquire knowledge about historical events Be present at Sunday Service See the beautiful glass paintings and impressive architectonics 5. Gandhi Chowk (Mall Road) GPO or Gandhi Chowk is a place in Dalhousie to enjoy a shopping tour and is a mall road in this small town. Visitors can buy traditional handicrafts from local markets and take gifts for themselves and their loved ones. The Himachal Handloom Industry Emporium and the Tibetan Market are among some of the famous shops at Gandhi Chowk from where one can buy memento, woolen clothes and much more. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Explore the Emporium on Thandi Sarak Buy traditional handiwork and keepsakes Pay a visit to Bhittico to get Kullu shawls, pashmina and angora 6. Ganji Pahari Ganji Pahari in Dalhousie offers its visitors an astounding view of snow-topped peaks. One has to trek to reach the peak that begins from Panchpula, and as this trek is easy to moderate, anyone can do it. Also named Bald Hill, Ganji Pahari is popular for its complete absence of vegetation on the hillock. Tourists can plan their winter trip to see a thick blanket of snow covering this hillock. Explore Ganji Pahari during dawn or sundown for the best experience. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Trekking Camping (advance booking is required) Watch eye-catching views of mountains 7. Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary has a wide range of luxurious meadows, thick deodar foliage, freshwater streams and more, making it a must-visit tourist attraction in the town for wildlife admirers. Kalatop means "black cap", which refers to the black forest enwrap in this wildlife sanctuary's highest summit. Various trekking and hiking trails are available inside the sanctuary, which makes up for a 