everages and snacks at local shops and stalls 10. Khajjiar Also referred to as "Mini Switzerland of India ", Khajjiar is a small town positioned at a distance of 20 km from Dalhousie. This place has a plentiful natural beauty that draws the attention of travelers from everywhere. Visit a small lake in the midst of grassland and click photos for memories. Visitors can get involved in fun activities like paragliding and create thousands of memories that will last evermore. The nine-hole golf course is the most popular part of Khajjiar, placed in the centre of luxurious greenery. For a great experience, travel here during winter to play in snow. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Savor local food Handicraft shopping Horse riding, paragliding, zorbing 11. Chamba Chamba is a Himalayan town in Himachal popular for its alluring prehistoric shrines, caves and monuments. It is a haven for a history enthusiast. Placed at an elevation of 996 meters, it sits on the Ravi River's banks. Few people know that Chamba is an unconventional place that provides natural beauty and tranquil environs. Also, not known by many, it is the campground for several camps in the great Himalayan ranges. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Trekking Witness eye-catching views of Pir Panjal ranges, Zanskar, and Dhauladhar Shop for traditional handiwork and artwork Attend the famous festivals of Minjar Mela (2nd Sunday of August), Suhi Mata Mela (March/April) 12. Dainkund Peak With the scenic views of snow-topped peaks and pleasing valleys, Dainkund Peak is amongst the most popular tourist attractions to explore in Dalhousie. Located at an elevation of 2755 meters above sea level, it is the highest point of this attractive hill town. Trekking to this peak is quite easy whether one is with family or in a couple. Visitors can follow the pathway laid with tall deodar trees and colorful fl