 the support of the weather. This weather supports the tourists for making some picture-perfect memories, and they can also take some scenic walks all around this tourist attraction. Not just one or two, there are many tourist attractions in this hill town of Himachal Pradesh that one can visit during their trip to Dalhousie and experience some of the most awesome things of their life. This article talks about all such tourist attractions of Dalhousie, which one should include in their list while planning a trip here. 1. Subhash Baoli Named after the Subhash Chandra Bose, a freedom fighter, this tranquil location in Dalhousie is an ideal spot to witness the natural beauty and relax in the calm environs. This place is a spring known to possess medicinal properties, and many people say they have treated and cured the health of Subhash Chandra too. Visitors can pay tribute to the freedom fighter here and enjoy an evening walk and picnic. The snow-dusted hillock catches the eye along the spring that cascades into a frosty stream. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Evening stroll near the spring Picnic with family and friends Loosen up in its calm environment 2. Garam Sadak It is a route in the Dalhousie that link Gandhi Chowk with Subhash Chowk and is amongst the undiscovered locations to explore in the small town. Visitors can enjoy the valley's picturesque view from the Thai road fringed with tall trees and luxurious greenery. Wandering around in this place is considered the most touristy thing to do in the town. In addition, visitors will be able to see extraordinary Tibetan Rock Paintings sculpted on the walls on the wayside. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Witness incredible scenes of the valley A leisurely stroll Watch beautiful Tibetan Rock Paintings carved on the roadside 3. Panchpula Panchpula is a preferred picnic area in the town, placed 