tico to get Kullu shawls, pashmina and angora 6. Ganji Pahari Ganji Pahari in Dalhousie offers its visitors an astounding view of snow-topped peaks. One has to trek to reach the peak that begins from Panchpula, and as this trek is easy to moderate, anyone can do it. Also named Bald Hill, Ganji Pahari is popular for its complete absence of vegetation on the hillock. Tourists can plan their winter trip to see a thick blanket of snow covering this hillock. Explore Ganji Pahari during dawn or sundown for the best experience. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Trekking Camping (advance booking is required) Watch eye-catching views of mountains 7. Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary has a wide range of luxurious meadows, thick deodar foliage, freshwater streams and more, making it a must-visit tourist attraction in the town for wildlife admirers. Kalatop means "black cap", which refers to the black forest enwrap in this wildlife sanctuary's highest summit. Various trekking and hiking trails are available inside the sanctuary, which makes up for a refined nature walk. Opening hours - 7:00 am to 6:00 pm Entry charges - fluctuates from season to season. Contact the officials before visiting the sanctuary. Activities to enjoy at the place: Be amused by the scenic views of the Pir Panjal range Have a taste of snacks and tea at a small tea stall Hiking and trekking Watching rich flora and fauna Stay in the small hostelry inside the site. 8. Satdhara Falls Surrounded by astounding views of the Chamba Valley, Satdhara Falls is considered one of the best attractions to explore in Dalhousie. The luxuriant green pine and deodar trees are worth witnessing, and the cool breeze caressing the face makes one feel refreshed. It is believed that this place contains mica, which is popular for its medicinal properties in treating and curing skin diseases. If one wants to go out for a peaceful nature stroll, then this is an ideal location for them. Additionally, the fragrance of flowers will vanish all the visitors' worries and hypnotize them with its charm. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry fee - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Picnic with loved ones Trek to the falls A beautiful nature walk Witness the picturesque charm Capture the breathtaking falls and their environs 9. Chamera Lake Chamera Lake is one of the great destinations to explore in Dalhousie and to enjoy a fun day out. It is a popular picnic spot for families and couples who wants to spend some quality time together. One can even enjoy some water activities here for an unforgettable time. Placed at an elevation of 763 meters above sea level, the lake is enveloped by dedodar conifers and snow-topped mountains. For a passionate photographer, Chamera Lake is amongst the inescapable locations in the town. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry fee - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Enjoy picnicking with family and friends Capture beautiful pictures of the lake Have fun doing boating, kayaking, canoeing and river rafting Have a taste of beverages and snacks at local shops and stalls 10. Khajjiar Also referred to as "Mini Switzerland of India ", Khajjiar is a small town positioned at a distance of 20 km from Dalhousie. This place has a plentiful natural beauty that draws the attention of travelers from everywhere. Visit a small lake in the midst of grassland and click photos for memories. Visitors can get involved in fun activities like paragliding and create thousands of memories that will last evermore. The nine-hole golf course is the most popular part of Khajjiar, placed in the centre of luxurious greenery. For a great experience, travel here during winter to play in snow. The place is open from Monday to Sunday Entry charges - None Activities to enjoy at the place: Savor local food Handicraft shopping Horse riding, paragliding, zorbing 11. Chamba Chamba is a Himalayan town in Himach